name: A&W Canada
description: Fast-food outlet serving up namesake root beer, plus burgers, chicken & fries.
address: A&W Canada, Champlain Square, 7092 Kerr St, Vancouver, BC V5S 4W2

detailed_reviews.review_text: My family loves this location and we probably bring the kids once a week as a treat. The food is always good quality and the staff are always very friendly and helpful. It s frequently quite busy here and I often see familiar faces of other regulars who must enjoy coming here too. Parking: Lots of parking depending on the time of day. Kid-friendliness: There s no play area or anything but they ve got high chairs and a kids meal.

My friend and I shared a Beyond Burger meal with sweet potatoes as our fries instead of normal potatoes and added onion rings to the side and root beer for drink. The food overall tasted great! The only thing is the onion rings were too salty  inedibly salty. A staff came by every once in a while and checked to make sure everything was still good and we had everything we wanted. Overall great experience at this A&W. I would 100% recommend coming here for good fast food experience. I should also mention that we came about an hour before they closed and they still treated their customers with a smile on their faces and were happy to serve.

Food was really tasty. I really like it because it s tasty like it s  really good! Staff is very nice, food comes quickly, and overall it was a great experience eating here. Here s a photo of our food(after) #DEVOURED
Food was absolutely fantastic. Freshly toasted buns with fresh ingredients. Service was great. We were greeted by the friendliest smile. Clean environment. Would definitely come back.

Impressed by the service at this location! I think it was the manager who took our order, an older Filipina. She was really good, and even though it was busy, she asked us if we enjoyed our food when we were finished. The two other staff we interacted with were very friendly as well. The fries were fresh and hot whereas they often arent at other locations. Will definitely be coming back to this one!

Fast food can be under rated. My simple craving for poutine satisfied me well that I m impressed how it was presented so well, perfectly made: fries, to gravy, to cheese and of course served on a real dish. I just had the best poutine ever! Best part  are the people who seemed to love what they re doing.
The food is good. The staffs are friendly, and the restaurant is always clean.

Visited A&W this morning to get breakfast. A delightful lady at the counter served me, Caitlyn I think it was. She brought the food to my table and even made sure to clean it up for me. Very cheerful young girl. This didn t feel like a fast food joint but more of a diner with A+ service. Would come again.
Iconic Canadian franchise, famous for their root beer.  Nice breakfast meal selection.

Ive never experienced service like this before. All the staff are really nice, and I can tell this branch is the best A&W. The food quality was amazing fresh and clean! Ill definitely visit again soon!

We usually come after summing time. All the personnel are super kind and they have a lot of patience with my kids who always ask to take something off but add some cheese or bacon. We also asked for a drink refill to go and we always got it.
Good & friendly service, quick too. Food always hot & any customization has not been an issue.
Their food is clean, and their service is very good.

Absolutely one of my favourite places to go. Staff is so friendly. Especially the manager (she has been here for a long time.. with short hair) she always remembers our family..asks how my kid and husband are. Always stops by to the table to check if everything is ok.  Nice to have someone remember who you are! Everything is hot..fresh..down to the breakfast.  I think they are the reason..ive gained 20 pounds in the last few years. I come here too much .  Always clean.  Very nice space.  You guys rock!

Super delicious sandwiches, very well prepared. Very tasteful beyond meat burger,  and the onion rings were crunchy to perfection. Very friendly and efficient staff. Meals were prepared fast (even special orders) and were served hot. Store was cleaned and tidy. Everything was perfect. Best A&W weve been so far. :)
The staff was very nice and she offered iced water for my kids. The kids enjoyed poutine and fries very much. The restaurant is clean too as they do cleaning regularly
Our fave branch in Vancouver! All Staff are very welcoming and always all smiles as we entered the place! Kudos to the team of Ms Milani! I used their washroom once and its clean and smells neat too!
Service is always good here, always friendly staff. Rated the food 3 stars today because my burger bun is a bit burnt. Food : 3/5
A great place. I enjoyed the food. I was attended by Clarita. Excellent customer service. I can give her 10/10 Food

Wonderful place with nothing much to say! It is a key component to my life and when I am in a pinch it is here to help me out. The staff is stellar to a galactic level with them being always to it no questions asked. And if you are asking about the food we ll see for yourself! (Also if you are around here with family morning plates here just bring me to heaven!) Kid-friendliness: Just a perfect place for family gatherings has enough room for a couple and kids!
The staff are always so friendly - Clarita especially! The service is exceptional and the food never disappoints. My favourite location by far!
They have consistently made fresh and tasty food amidst a kind and welcoming atmosphere. It feels like you are eating at home amongst friends and family. The food is the best in town.
Good service! The place is small but personnel are very friendly and the food is always good.
Great location, great food, great service. Gurleen was very helpful in turning my order of several separate items into a combo so that I can have extra to order more. Food : 5/5
This A&W is very clean, making you feel comfortable to eat here. The staff members are friendly and helpful. This is so far the best A& W location I ve been in Vancouver.

This is an awesome location! The food is always top tier and always comes out fresh. The staff is always super nice and interactive. The restaurant is always clean and the managers are friendly aswell! This is a good location for some fast food in champlain

The staff on this A&W branch is amazing specially the ones assigned in their counters. Burgers & fries were serve hot and fast not to mention the ice cold refreshing Rootbeer. Parking: The Champlain place is great if you are in a hurry since a lot of parking space is available.
All clean All kind All good foods This place is my absolute favorite! Just go ahead and order anything from the menu if you want to leave with a big smile after your meal! No.1 A&W in B.C!!
I had a fantastic experience at A&W Champlain Square. The food was delicious, the staff were friendly, and the restaurant was impeccably clean. I ll definitely be back!
Super friendly staff and very clean. Always come here for dad daughter dates as the kiddo loves the people and fries here
Had a lovely dinner with great service provided by the kind staff. The space is nicely clean and enjoyable to enjoy one s meal

The two staff members were hustling to keep the busy line moving all while maintaining smiles and great attitudes. Definitely a gem among the many possible options available.
The burgers and fries are delicious. The crew here (especially Sanya) are so nice, helpful and care for customers.
We come here because its near our home, but the staff have always been very friendly and always have a little something to give our kids when we eat there. One of our fav quick family meal spots!

Hazel is such a sweet and friendly. Good service towards customer. Food are good. Excellent! Food : 5/5

Are all the A&Ws like this? Im not a fan of fast food places but I came here one morning with my son as not much else was open in the plaza at 8am, and was blown away.  Not sure if Im just not up to speed with the changes at A&W, but I felt like a was in a diner.  The place is super clean, with good service to start. But the food and how its presented is the best.  Fresh eggs, any style, toast, sausage, and bacon, on a real plate, with metal utensils.  Orange juice served In a frosted glass, coffee served in a nice mug.  The hashbrown in metal paper lined basket.  All served on a metal, not plastic tray.  This fast food place is doing it right.  Cudos to whoever is charge of all the changes. It definitely made my short list of place to go for a quick bite.
Loved it here  you feel comfortable very good  to sit down and eat here

description: Classic, long-running fast-food chain known for its burgers & fries.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Great Toddler/Mommy McDs with large, enclosed play place, climbing structure 2y+, ordering/pay station inside play area, high chairs, NO wifi access, bathroom not in play area, & dirty but not horrid. They had pancakes allday in happy meal & lots of parking. I d recommend, if you need a place to work & eat , while children run in circles screaming. There are many screaming children. Kid-friendliness: Bathrooms, enclosed play area, large climbing structure with slide & padded area. 2yr -12yrs, high chairs, room for strollers, trash, bathrooms Wheelchair accessibility: All on one level, handicapped parking, room in restaurant for wheelchairs

This McDonalds has a great location spot next to Science World and the stadium. Surprisingly, it has free parking with a big parking lot. Its open 24/7 for dine in, take out, and drive through. Kid-friendliness: Has an indoor playground

Well the reason Im giving them a 5 star is because there security caught the thief who actually stole the kids meal I had on the table so when I took little man I was looking after to the restroom so guy took his food and his box of doughnuts and actually drank out of my coffee cup but they handled with respect and I appreciated that from them plus the other people around us where super nice
It was fairly quick with a full line up frendly staff on the drive through

Consistently THE WORST drive thru service. I am asked to pull over and wait a minimum of 7 minutes every time I go. And every time, I have to walk in and demand my food...AND every single time the sauces I PAID FOR are not in the bag. The place is an absolute circus with food delivery guys, homeless, bums, addicted people lurking about everywhere. Its a zoo and the service is atrocious. Im DONE.
This Mc Donald center is fully automated. You can customize everything. Large variety in the menu and nice salad that I havent seen in any other branches before.
Changed my life. The finest 5 star cuisine Ive ever had, how have I never heard of this place? Its like McMagic in my mouth!

In the middle of a heat dome and it was unbelievably hot outside ... walking into the restaurants lovely, air conditioned interior was such a relief! It was crazy busy and totally chaotic but all the staff we dealt with were so friendly and pleasant. There was lots of parking outside and no line-ups at the ordering kiosks and the washroom was spotless. Altogether a great visit.
I have purchased 4 cars from these guys over the years and their service has been outstanding. I highly recommend them to anyone looking for a used car in excellent condition!!!!

I have Never experienced this at a McDonalds. Not the staff members fault but if there was more cashiers at the front maybe that could have been avoided.

Great food n drinks

This used to be one of dirtiest McDonalds in north America due to homelessness and people with low personal care in its surroundings.  Washrooms where dirty, a lot of people very spending more than usual time in the lobby. BUT NOW!!!!!!!!! After having doors at its North West entrance closed, and having security at its main entrances, there are no more unrelated people hanging around. Even doordash and uber eats receive their deliveries from the security officer making it even more professional. Now I can tell the management worked hard to re- establish this place. I really hope this place holds their security officer which is very polite and professional. I also hope other McDonalds with busy downtown traffic to employ security officers , especially once covid is over and night clubs re opens.
Best time to come to this location is late at night when theres only several groups dining and not a lot of people in line waiting for their food. The staff are very nice here.
Nice place
I ordered from Uber eats. Incredibly fast! My burger was made to my specifications. Perfectly. Lol thank you for my cookie! An excellent encounter! I love you guys!
The free fries are too good lol.. the new cigarettes
Great for a quick snack any time of the day. Menu as expected.
The staff are so aware and gracious I asked them for additional condiments and they immediately gave me Thank you so much I ll always buy from them
Very consistent! I think they have yet to mess up my order and Ive visited this location MANY times. Plus the staff are friendly and have a great sense of urgency.
Quiet place. Nice view. For the rest, just an ordinary MacDonalds :)))
Great stop when walking along the creek because they have a washroom
It was spectacular. Food elevates mood and the fine dining experience elevated me to hitherto unknown realms of clarity and inner peace.
This McDonalds food was pretty good. I liked my big Mac like I always get.  And always the best after a fat joint...
My first experience with this restaurant was amazing but the location was great and easy for us to find and the price was great

I absolutely love McDonalds coffee and have no shame in saying it! Theyre coffee isnt too hot when you get it, and the taste is just so good! If youre ever looking for just a black coffee and dont want to break the bank..... Orrrr seriously just really want a good coffee, get theirs. I drink mine with 4 cream (yes, always and no it hasnt made me fat haha) I love that I buy 7 coffees and get a free one as well! The food is alright as well if you like carby stuff haha

[REVIEWED IN OCTOBER 2019] This McDonalds is a nice, large, but busy location, with plenty of comfortable seating areas to settle in. I came here & paid so I could use their WiFi to play World of Warcraft. Found out WoW was unplayable for whatever reason, despite other online games working okay. Rated 5 stars despite this disappointment, but its a pretty awesome McDonalds location. 24 hours at that!
It was nice but wierd. A stranger cleared it ,told me I should sit there, I ate my big Mac, ( alone but not) with barriers,I had a covid good time . I guess Today I made it to 59 yrs..

The paladins slinging grease in this citadel of soberiety are the last line of defense against the quarreling, drunken horde stumbling back toward the skytrain after striking out in Gastown. God bless them in their solemn duty.
Its nice and clean. The staff were all very friendly and helpful. McDonalds does everything right it seems!
This McDonalds is one of the best in Vancouver.  Very friendly and helpful staff provide a very pleasant overall order experience.  Keep up the great work
Nice day

Very sloppy burgers leaves you running straight to the bathroom! UPDATE: Since Ive last left this review. Ive notice that this particular McD has been making their burgers more with care, rather than the sloppy mess that i have been getting from here before.
Good location. Not much different than any other one but they are quick and give great service. Can get crazy busy at some hours.
Very well kept cleanliness of restaurant two thumbs up no mess ups on my order as well another plus

This location is one of the busiest McDonald s in town. I really give the employees credit for staying relatively cheerful throughout the day, even though this location gets quite a colourful variety of patrons.
I went thru the drive thru and it didnt take too long. The food was great service was good.
Cause of whip cream on my hot cakes umm good

Oh man. Only come here if youre drunk or high. If youre sober, you better be going through the drive-thru. Otherwise, youll be seeing all the magnificent disgusting people who come here on Friday night on Wednesday afternoon.
Always fast. I order from the app and get it for pick up and its usually ready by the time Im there.
Not really sure why they were nervous during the work
The seating situation has changed due to covid-19 but the place is very clean and hand sanitizer are everywhere and ready to be used.
Very busy but fast service coffee was perfect they made it just right cause I like my coffee on the cold side thanks keep up the good work
Staff are great. They can handle the chaos...  Have always had a good experience here, order is always correct. Staff is kind and helpful
Dont know how long McDonalds have been in town but I was really surprised by how good the dining experience is. I think it will catch on.
If you have kids. You can dine and let your kids play

The service is really good but the boys washroom is really dirty I am really scared of the washroom but the food and service is very very good the mangers are very nice also the soft serve ice cream that they make is really big and yummy
Excellent fast service. Cleaning person Wednesday am was very friendly and efficient. Meal was hot. Excellent all around outlet.

Just love the service of this place....   I had a wound on my hand which started bleeding suddenly... So I asked them a band aid... Nd the staff nd the manager was so nice... That they offered me the first aid asap..  thank you so much for your help
Restaurant was clean first friendly service order was correct and served hot and fresh.
For lunch today, I had a Dijon Onion Burger, & it was delicious. It was only $2.99. I should have had two, however, as one wasnt quite enough to satisfy my hunger!
Busy restaurant with large parking lot. Staffs are friendly and efficient. Foods are within the standard. I appreciated and thanks they have a security guard in the restaurant.
Big one, not so clean    but cleaner than most others
Went thru the drive thru and the service was very fast and the staff were polite and they were able to get our whole order correct  :)
Bah dah dah daaah i am lovin it and alittle secret smiles are free;)
In near downtown, this is the best McDonalds. The most I like is, this has parking lot. The cons are you will see lots of homeless, washroom is dirty.
Excellent quality control on the chicken nuggets. Consistently deliver a highly nutritious meal.
Outside clean washroom clean too good foods chicken  fish so good,coffee  can u make  a little hot drink better thx
Busy, basic not trendy but they never let down.. good food and good service.
Food service is awesome and was clean in the dining area. Cant complain at all.
The food is good love it its so awesome n the bigmac meal I love the most
Was pretty good they one of the good McDonalds around always clean and they treat the customer like customers no judgemental all
Despite location being somewhat sketchy, this location manages to keep clean and provide good service and food cooked to exacting standards.
Same McDonalds as everywhere. Crazy fast service and automated order kiosks everywhere! Kudos to the staff for being good at handling the local demographics of the DTES area.
probably the most cursed mcdonalds in Vancouver however immensely blessed at the same time
Surprisingly clean, staff must be incredibly patient. Theyve rarely ever messed up my order
Wonderful play structure my kids enjoy. Also, new upstairs dinning area is clean, and airly.
Friendly staff and good cooks. One of the best McDonalds in Greater Vancouver, conveniently located downtown by Science World, Via (train and bus station), Skytrain and close to Chinatown.
Gotta love McDonalds    Food was perfect as usual here too!
Lots of parking spaces. Clean place with security agent always available. Staff are quick and good in service.
All McDonalds are the same however this particular one has the highest ratio of junkie to staff in the Pacific Northwest. Thats a fact.
Floors werent sticky at all
It was busy but staff were very efficient and organized.
Good location and good service even in the pandemic. Access to washroom too and security personnel by the entrance for assistance.
Dont blame them if youre fat.  They have salad and its not their fault if you dont choose it.

detailed_reviews.review_text: I went to McDonalds Still Creek yesterday at around 16:30. It s a nice place with very easy parking. Staff are kind and very professional, service is great! I also noticed that the Drive through is fast as well. Food : 2/5 |

When I took my first sip of the iced coffee that I purchased for $1 it washed away all negative memories of my gambling sessions and all the chicanery that is employed to extract money from me. This iced drink provides me with so much upside while putting down very little capital. Thanks you, I will not be clown shoed again
Whoever packed my order took the time to write a note about my iced coffee and I really appreciated the service!

I dont go to McDonalds very often but this one is my favourite. Very clean, spacious dining area both inside and outside and really fast-paced! My favourite items here are hash browns and chicken MacGuffin. Smoothies are good too especially the ones with mango and pineapple.

I really like sitting on the upper floor with my food. Its has plenty of space to dine in with different table options. It has a separate play place where my kids can play while I am having my coffee. They also have refill station upstairs and Washrooms, accessible washroom is downstairs. They have a separate room for Kids party, I saw birthday decorations and cake one time. It has a lot of parking as well.

As much as I feel empathetic towards the crew members that work here, it s just too busy when you re close to the BCIT on weekdays. Otherwise, the production team is doing amazing. The service is great, the food is decent. Thank you McDonald s.

Mic-ie D so fast so good this location is so big and has been here forever I used to go to this location with my dad when I was little. The place has not changed since I was a kid. Recommendation = Fries + ice cream.       +
$4 combo deal for bacon and egg mcmuffin and medium coffee

This location is big in two floor and has patio seating Relatively clean Staff are kind and understanding. I had some issues with McDonalds app, they helped me with that and actually offered free Coke, fries and one shake to make me happy Convenient parking location and kids play also provided but closed due to Covid

This meal had me feeling like I I I m in the stars tonight. This is getting heavy Can you hear the bass boom? Im ready (woo hoo) Life is sweet as honey Yeah, this beat cha-ching like money, huh Disco overload, Im into that, Im good to go Im diamond, you know I glow up Hey, so lets go. So cheesy BTS joke aside the sauces were actually really good! Substituted the coke that s part of the meal for a coffee Frappuccino and it was very good overall. Staff at the drive through were friendly and efficient. No complaints at all.

McDs is our summer go to.  Got lemonade, kid played in the play area, A/C, inflation friendly if youre ordering off the value menu and use app promos. Only critique is the parking could be scarce depending on the time of day but thats about it. Kid-friendliness: Theres a play place which is partially separated in the upper floor.  Well decorated, very vibrant.  Remember to bring socks.
The best fast food. Quick service with a smile. One of the greatest franchises on earth. The outlet at Still Creek is my favourite! Always get my orders correct and friendly/polite!
One of the coolest McDonalds ever! Lots of bright windows and the place was very clean. Good job staff :)
Great food here. Everything was hot when we received, the restaurant was clean and food tasted great. Didnt have to wait long, and the kids were happy.

I and 3 others just wanted a snack so my oder just z cheese burgers extra pickle, onion, and ketchup, mustard .. Now I know this is small but its what I wanted and for the extra.. Non existent..  Basically now when I get the food I check everything before I leave.
The manager on shift tonight was so kind to us. I wish I had gotten his name but he was wonderful.
Food was excellent and the service is always prompt, friendly. Great place to eat.

This is the best McDonalds i have been to for a very long time. Very quick service the line moved so smooth, food was fresh and hot, order was correct and staff was very friendly. Store front kept very clean.

I had prejudice against McDonalds before until their restaurants changed for good. Every McDonalds now is top notch. Clean, modern...its a pleasure to pass by. A&W and Wendys restaurant  need to start working.
Beautiful and gracefully place for coffee, breakfast. I come here two or three times a week with my wife and friends   . Thanks!
Large popular location with tons of seating. Fully app supported where you can order from your car or from any table you pick. Consistent flavor like what you would expect from any McDonald s.
You guys made my night. And everything was delicious
This is a great location. Standard fast food and ok service but a great location.

Yesterday morning was quite stressful for McD HQ. It seems as they were having computer/ticket printer issues causing anxious diners to inquire on their order. Glad to witness the miss with the colorful hair still prioritized to help an elderly and his order of five hot beverages to his car. A tip of the cap towards the staff!
Im really sad to get this mcmuffin. Some parts are burned. This muffin is so hard as plastic. I can eat that without muffins. Unfortunately, I got two Mcmuffin... Guess what next happens.
Best McDonalds Ive been to. great juicy pattys
One of the best MacDonald in lower mainland, I believe this location is one of their staff training center Kid-friendliness: Kids friendly

Great quick and efficient drive though. Its also good that its close to Freeway and Lougheed Highway so its easy to get back on your traveling route. It can be tricky getting in or out of parking lot. If dinning in can be busy with long wait times.

Nice clean McDonalds.  Very busy location and they do a remarkable job keeping things moving.  Always fresh and golden fries. The parking lot tends to get flooded during rain storms. Lots of seating area.  The ordering and waiting area is too small for the volume they do.  The upstairs area is a good spot to enjoy your McDonalds.
It is good place to stay for relax.

I dont mean the quality is bad but the size. That apply to all McDonalds. Food is not worth. I only buy coffee but coffee quality is not stable. Other McDonalds are the same. Sometimes, I got just brown water without any coffee taste.

Come here pretty regularly. Drive thru service is always quick. Prices on some items are a little cheaper than some of the other Mcd restaurants in the area. Never had an issue with curbside pickup either. The dining-in experience is above average compared to other locations. I have come here for years, and plan to continue for years to come

Did not grab her name but the lady that was working today around 12-1P, who was particularily stocking the straws, lids, and cleaning the trays deserves a lot more credit and appreciation than people show her. Yes, its simple tasks but a task / role that many overlook, perhaps including this company itself. As shes most likely just another sin number on a piece of paper to most. In truths, its because its a simple task and many consider it needy and the right / entitlement to neglect her and her position. As a senior manager myself, I see value in her role. The task itself becomes challenging as it is all about repitions day in day out. If everyone could do this, they already wouldve. The times I frequent this establishment while shes away or after her shift, the condiments etc are always EMPTY. Thank you for hiring her so us customer can constantly have straws, lids, condiments at our disposal. A little goes a long. Hope this translates / transpires into a wage increase for her. I will be acknowledging her that Ive left this review to have her be recognize. You store managers should do the same.
How it looks like during COVID-19 in the dinning area.
Huge seating area including second floor with play area. Amazing kids loved it Food : 5/5
Busy and good place to drink coffee. It has nice parking place to park your car.

This McDonalds has the best night drive thru in the world! The server is hilarious, engaging, prompt and Im pretty sure he threw in a heel click with glee when he ran outside to deliver my food. Thanks dude for brightening my evening!

This is one of the better McDonald s with a really nice large dine-in area on the second floor and clean washrooms (with no weird people squatting the booths). It s a little out of the way and only accessible by driving probably

McDonald s has been really proactive with COVID-19 safety. Prior to the pandemic their restaurants were among the cleanest fast food places. Now they are even cleaner. The food is predictable and the coffee is really quite good.

Depending on the staff that are on shift, this McDonalds gives me faith in humanity. The food is always fresh here and usually really good. Havent messed up my order yet. The people taking your order arent brick walls. Never had an unreasonable wait here. Overall a stellar example of what all McDonalds should aspire to be.

This location is the best. Heard it was the head office (in BC? Not sure). There are some staff members who aren t very considerate listeners when it comes to customers with accents or lower English language proficiency (my folks have been felt shunned for their English... luckily for them, I wasn t there ), but most of the times the staff there are friendly. They are cool with giving condiments (as some places will charge you), and their second floor area is a lovely place to sit and just chill.  Parking is free, but watch-out as some lots are now designated for other businesses there.
I dropped my ice cream but they gave a replacement one! Great customer service at this location.

Good McDonalds location. The servers are really nice, and the food comes out really quickly. Well organized, and very clean. I havent had any problems with this one. The food is very well made, for McDonalds quality.

This is probably one of the largest McDonalds Ive ever visit. It has two stories and LOTS of seats. Food came real quick and we enjoyed the stay. Though it is not that convenient to visit if you dont have a car, but you can pretty much enjoy McDonalds anywhere else too.
Makes me feel good to be here. The staffs are peppy and upbeat. Never had a wrong order. The whole system is like a well oiled machine. Good job! I always love coming here instead of other McDonalds.

Great, clean restaurant that is one of the most elegant McDonalds restaurant Ive been so far. It doesnt really look like a fast food chain from the outside, ample parking and drive thru service is fast as well. There are mobile app parking stalls as well if you are in a hurry to get food.
Was there at 12:30 on Thursday, during lunch Rush, the Lady on Till was amazing, taking drive through orders, running for her self and giving every customer the best service.
This is one time they didnt screw up our order. Are they getting better? Only time will tell.
Had an issue with a mobile order and they resolved it quickly and even gave me the sandwiches for free since something went wrong on the app end. Their manager was helpful and very friendly.
Friendly and timely service. We came in ordered something like 8 breakfast burger and sides and the staff were patient and attentive. Would definitely come again of I am in the area.

Went too this location for lunch, lady was at the door only letting a few people order at a time the ketchup pumps were also taken away. Really nice bike path/paved trail right across from this mc donalds.

Located in a calm area in North Burnaby, this Mc Donalds has lots of space for parking, online pick-ups, accessible park spots, short lines for the drive-thru and a great view if you want to dine-in in the mezzanine. Its my favorite Mc Donalds in the region, by far.

Updated: January 13, 2019 I had the pleasure of dealing with Sarah the manager. She was fantastic and has earned a 5 star review Old:It s rarely up to par here. Just sad because it s head office. This his always been drive thru servive. I did go in once. It s super nice inside, tv, upstairs lounge fireplace. Nice stuff.

Surinder in the drive thru is always a delight. She takes my order promptly, professionally and with a smile. After paying for my morning coffee her words of  thank you dear  always starts my day on a positive note. Give that woman a raise!

McDonalds is trying a new system. Today, we went to the McDonalds on Willingdon, near the freeway. We ordered and were given a disc to take to a table that allowed a staff member to find our table and bring our food to us. After our food arrived, a staff member followed up to be sure everything was fine. It was nice to not have to hang around in the ordering area, waiting for our food.
Kudos to the Manager/Supervisor of this branch for finding my wallet that I left on the couch! I am so thankful she found it and kept it in a safe place!
Best McDonalds Ive been in. Above average service, personable staff, very clean restaurant, food was exactly to order, hot and fresh. A refreshing experience, thank you!
Hi, our recent visit proved to be worthy, fries were perfect and so was my filet o fish.

Ordered a pot of coffee muffins and danishes werent ready waiting waiting and waiting make me late for work this is the new online ordering and pickup service not sure when its going to be a good hopefully McDonalds respond by a couple extra muffins while I wait here..... well went back that day an they gave me full refund just what I wanted ... went and tried it the next day and it was way better thanks McD s good job

The Mcdonalds headquarters for Canada I think. Service is always fast and quality of food pretty much the peak of what you can get from McDonalds. It would make sense as this is where corporate eyes are always watching and people are training to the McDonalds Gold Standard. Great place to hang out while waiting for car-related stuff at the nearby dealerships.
Charlotte is the best. Very kind and amazing customer service. She deserves a promotion.
5/5. Classic. Timeless. Reliable. McDonalds never disappoints be it breakfast, lunch, dinner or an illicit but desperately necessary 11pm stroll through the drivethrough. Cant go wrong.
Rated in the drive through, easy, quick and efficient. No comment on the food, its what you would expect. Vegetarian options: Sold options Parking: Lots of room

This is the best McDonalds experience in the area. Large restaurant with upstairs and outdoor seating. Music plays throughout (outside too, theres even a fireplace outside to keep you warm!) I also appreciate the 24/7 service.

The service is like all Mcdicks, hit or miss, mostly hit. The restaurant however is freaking awesome, its huge, if you stay downstairs you may think it sucks but once you go upstairs there is always sitting space and they have tvs upstairs too. On the downside as an adult with no kids, they also have a whole playground upstairs and sometimes the kids are loud, but overall, this Macdonald is a nice one to go to.
Great location, good number of parking spots available. Staff are friendly and service is reasonably fast. I never have trouble finding a spot to eat even during the busiest hours.
This MacDonalds has one of the best environments in Vancouver. The outside patio has a good open view of the surrounding landscaping. The inside has a fireplace and lots of natural light.
They made my sandwich quick and it tasted great, better than normal mcdonalds. I tried the chicken mcgriddle and it was blessed. Definitely reccomend it. I put lettuce and mayo on mine.
A great place to grab a meal. Our order was correct, hot and tasted great. The Staff were very friendly and quick to accommodate our requests. Thanks McDs
Real good service. The staff were most excellent.!  The manager actually made me smile. And was uplifting. I hope you go places Sir..   thank-you for all Ure kindness i really needed it today..!
Like any other McDonalds. Drive thru staff were really friendly. Fast service.
Flagship store, at least when it opened. Quick, efficient with friendly and very well trained staff. Food also finest McQuality.
This McDonalds is nicely maintained and clean.  Food is typical McDonalds, its ok and not bad.  There are plenty of sitting spaces.  They even deliver the good to your table.
Still Creek Dr. Is THE  BEST  McDonalds to order from , great crew always follow instructions and food is amazing. These people ROCK !!! Keep up the great work. Cheers
My son loves their newly renovated play area!   Service was great!  They didnt get mad at me for order a burger with mobile service.  :-P

Great Mc Donalds location. Clean, spacious, 2 floors with a kids play area in the top floor.  Friendly staff. Meal was tasty and fresh, complying with the high-quality standards of the Mc Donalds chain. My kids love that place.
Always got my orders right and drive thru most time faster then inside. Clean and large sitting area.

The staff here work fast to clear the line and food deliver out on time, the dinning area is comfortable with a nice fireplace in the middle and play area for kids is not big but my kiss still having fun, overall is a good experience in here
Quick service, great McDonalds quality food. They offer table service here and its great. Messed up my order once, made it right. Very happy with this location.
Great food and free wifi free parking the restaurant has heating making it very cozy to spend time inside it even has a fireplace and sofas.

I have to say just left McDonalds guess someone called in sick. They had the night maintenance man on cashier taking orders best experience ever need to give that boy a raise and put them on the till.

Great McDonalds that has an abundance of power outlets but you cant order food to your table because McDonalds wants to FORCE you to use their app which i refuse to. Guess Im saving money, jokes on McDonalds.
This is the best McDonalds store for the parents with their young kids. We loved the play zone and the craft zone. Im not sure whether the craft zone is temporary though)
I liked there customer service, staff is very friendly. I always like McDonalds for their quick service and hot meals

Its a McDonalds - but a very nice one. Totally modern with electronic order machines, two floors, play place, pop machines on both floors, great views, optional meeting room to rent and the nicest, most helpful McDonalds staff Ive ever dealt with.

McDonalds gets beat up a lot by folks, but lets face it, its delicious. Regardless of if you view it as a pleasure or a guilty pleasure you can rely on this chain to produce tasty food at a moments notice.
It was Halloween day and a lady all dressed up opened the door for me an some other customers wishing us Happy Halloween. I really like this McDonalds restaurant: big, quiet, nice staff...
I go to the drive through everyday. Service is excellent.  Great friendly staff with a good sense of humor .I always leave with a smile or a laugh.
Very busy place during lunch hour. Great location. Fast service. Ace all around.
What she order? FISH FILET. My favorite thing here. Sometimes I get a salad when I feel like eating healthier. My go to place other than Churchs Chicken.
Clean, fast and friendly.  Very nice place, would go back again.
Spacious, clean and has everything! Great place for family get away. We will be back!
Best Mcdonalds, Drive thru in the morning  Is very efficient
Brought my doggy as I was getting my truck serviced across the street they came out and baby sat him for me brought him water wile I order then brought my food out to me too on the patio!! Awesome!
Probably the best McDonalds in the area. The staff is friendly, food is cooked fast and the place itself is pretty cozy. The perfect place for finishing your works leftovers.
Very friendly staff. Made everything fresh with reasonable wait time. Great night crew. Thank you.
The staff are super friendly and helpful.  They consistently go over and above what you would expect from a fast food restaurant

I dont normally go to mcdonalds, but this mcdonalds was awesome!! Its such a relaxing enviroment upstairs. The view is Nice and the food was pretty good! I would go back for sure just for a coffee and to hang out
Still the best for budget eaters, depends on the location and staff attitude, Mc will stay public number one fast food to go!

We came here when it was super busy at around 11:30pm, we were going through the drive through and we were frustrated at first because it was taking a while but the lady at the drive through, Ren, was honestly amazing and so kind to us, even though the environment was clearly very stressful and the person taking our order (another employee) got our order wrong.

detailed_reviews.review_text: The service is fast and the food served is always fresh and hot. The self order checkout are easy to use and are always clean. The crew their is friendly and make sure that we understand what food we need and sometimes gives suggestions of what is better option. The dine in is cozy and wide especially in the sunshine it looks fabulous.

I usually pass by this McDonalds on the way to work using their mobile app which is very convenient. I usually use the drive-thru. The place looks neat and clean and the crew are very friendly, especially. Susan D Which is a delight to hear her in the drive-thru speaker and the window when youre passing through. Their coffee is very good as well as their muffins

The service is fast and the food served is always fresh and hot. The self order checkout are easy to use and are always clean. The crew their is friendly and make sure that we understand what food we need and sometimes gives suggestions of what is better option. The dine in is cozy and wide especially in the sunshine it looks fabulous. Recently they were giving free samples for their new ice cream and it was yummm. The parking lot has nice flowers and space for parking cars is wide. If I am nearby, I always get an ice cream for sure from here. The patio here though small is good for sitting during summer times.

google keeps asking me to review McDonalds even though this review means nothing to everyone everywhere. You all have an opinion on McDonalds and a strangers words on the internet isnt going to change that. I have attached a photo of one of my orders. I like ordering decaf completely black to see how the cashiers respond to the abomination. Thank you

Social distancing and limited seating in effect. Hand sanitizer at entrance/exit. Arrows to indicate traffic flow one way. Plexiglass shields at cashier as well as food pick up counter. All great safety measures to make you feel safe while ordering or eating here. Update:  service/atmosphere has gone downhill since reopening. Was there Friday night and took well over 6-7min to get my order. I ordered on the app. Restaurant was a mess. I could see kitchen was a mess too with fries all over the floor of the fry station. Staff was standing around chatting in kitchen and in no rush to serve customers. By the way, my fries were cold too. Very disappointed.
Something about music list, whoever picked those songs, it s all contemporary and amazing as to make me stay for long and write reviews Cheers Food
This place is well organized, very clean and with great customer service. First time 5 stars for McDonalds.

I bought for my kids lunch here a double burger and a happymeal.  But when I brought it home my son found it was a single burger. When I went to them the next day with a complaint, the administrator gave me a double burger and happymeal for free. A very positive experience. Thanks to the restaurant and manager.
good location, I have ordered McFish this time.. I can say it was not the freshest fried pattie, but I understand it was around 1.15am.. so no regrets.. it satisfied me and thats all what matter

Good food at reasonable prices and lots of free parking. Good for families on a budget especially when traveling or visiting Vancouver. Includes a playground for children. Vegetarian options: Special request menus available Dietary restrictions: Requests for special orders with extra veggies or salads are available Parking: Large lot for parking and other free parking on Southside of resturant Kid-friendliness: Lots of room for families and large seating areas, including playground. Wheelchair accessibility: Fully available

Im giving this McDonalds 5 stars simply because I needed to blow my nose after getting off the bus and having to get on the SkyTrain.  Why didnt I just go to the Timmies literally just a few steps away right across the street from the SkyTrain station you ask?  Oh I did.  But sadly at 730am they had no toilet paper in their public washroom.  So, wtg, McDonalds!!; One more runny nose saved.  Thank you.

Accessibility Information - This review was prepared by my Social Studies 9 class after a site visit and an interview with the manager. We went to local McDonalds located in 15574 Fraser Hwy to find out if this McDonalds was accessible for people who use wheelchairs or scooters. We were able to find things that made this place accessible. First, there were two accessible parking spots available right beside the entrance to the store. Second, the doors of the store could be opened by pressing a button that is placed on the wall beside the door. There is a ramp for wheelchairs and scooters to go up. Also, they are planning to get new doors so that it is easier for wheelchair and scooter users to use. The bathroom doors do not have buttons on the wall, but the sink, the toilet paper, the dryer, and the soap were placed low so that they can be easily accessed by wheelchair and scooter users. The aisles in the restaurant are wide enough for wheelchair and scooter users to go through.

Wifi speed is about 14 Mbps download. Not a kids concentrated area so the freebies for kids such as drawing paper, color crayons, balloons have decent availability. Theres this manager whos energetic and I like his attitude towards work and customer service. He seems to recognize many regular customers and they like to have a short chat with him.
